org.nasdanika.engineering

Interface Decision

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Adaptable, Aim, Alignable, Capability, Endeavor, EngineeredCapability, EObject, Issue, Marked, ModelElement, NamedElement, Notifier, Period
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DecisionImpl

    public interface Decision
extends Issue, Aim
    A representation of the model object 'Decision'.

    The following features are supported:

    • Effective Start
    • Effective End
    • Supercedes
    • Superceded By
    • Resolution
    See Also:
    EngineeringPackage.getDecision()

    • Method Detail

      • getEffectiveStart

        Date getEffectiveStart()
        Returns the value of the 'Effective Start' attribute. Date when this decision goes into effect once it is available (done). If not set, decision goes into effect once it is in a done status.
        Returns:
        the value of the 'Effective Start' attribute.
        See Also:
        setEffectiveStart(Date), EngineeringPackage.getDecision_EffectiveStart()

      • setEffectiveStart

        void setEffectiveStart(Date value)
        Sets the value of the 'Effective Start' attribute.
        Parameters:
        value - the new value of the 'Effective Start' attribute.
        See Also:
        getEffectiveStart()

      • getEffectiveEnd

        Date getEffectiveEnd()
        Returns the value of the 'Effective End' attribute. Date when decision stops being in effect if it was in effect before. If not set, the decision is effective indefinitely if it is in a done status.
        Returns:
        the value of the 'Effective End' attribute.
        See Also:
        setEffectiveEnd(Date), EngineeringPackage.getDecision_EffectiveEnd()

      • setEffectiveEnd

        void setEffectiveEnd(Date value)
        Sets the value of the 'Effective End' attribute.
        Parameters:
        value - the new value of the 'Effective End' attribute.
        See Also:
        getEffectiveEnd()

      • getSupercedes

        EList<Decision> getSupercedes()
        Returns the value of the 'Supercedes' reference list. The list contents are of type Decision. It is bidirectional and its opposite is 'Superceded By'. Decisions which this decision supercedes once (if ever) it goes into effect.
        Returns:
        the value of the 'Supercedes' reference list.
        See Also:
        EngineeringPackage.getDecision_Supercedes(), getSupercededBy()

      • getSupercededBy

        EList<Decision> getSupercededBy()
        Returns the value of the 'Superceded By' reference list. The list contents are of type Decision. It is bidirectional and its opposite is 'Supercedes'. Decisions which (will) supercede this decision when (if ever) they are effective.
        Returns:
        the value of the 'Superceded By' reference list.
        See Also:
        EngineeringPackage.getDecision_SupercededBy(), getSupercedes()

      • getResolution

        String getResolution()
        Returns the value of the 'Resolution' attribute. Documentation of what has been decided (decision process outcome).
        Returns:
        the value of the 'Resolution' attribute.
        See Also:
        setResolution(String), EngineeringPackage.getDecision_Resolution()
